Here's how I do it: if I get inspiration for a new story I write down a bit of an outline and a few notes, and then I write the scene that sparked that burst of inspiration in the first place. Then, if the story really grabbed me, I might keep writing, but otherwise I'll go back to whatever I was writing before. Usually I just need to get that one particular idea out of my head and down on paper so that I free up my brain for what I actually want to work on. Having random ideas floating around in my mind is hugely distracting
